Here's how to handle each scenario with modern MSTest (3.9+) attributes:

```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class MyTests
{
    private string? _tempFile;

    // 1. Windows-only: skip on Linux/macOS
    [TestMethod]
    [OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
    public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
    {
        var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\...", "Key", null);
        Assert.IsNotNull(value);
    }

    // 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)
    [TestMethod]
    [CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
    public void RenderFrame_ProducesValidOutput()
    {
        var frame = GpuRenderer.RenderFrame();
        Assert.IsNotNull(frame);
    }

    // 3. Flaky external API — retry up to 3 times
    [TestMethod]
    [Retry(3)]
    public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast()
    {
        var forecast = await WeatherClient.GetForecastAsync();
        Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
    }

    // 4. Temp file cleanup — [TestCleanup] runs even on failure
    [TestMethod]
    public void Export_WritesValidFile()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
        Exporter.WriteToFile(_tempFile);
        Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (_tempFile is not null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
        {
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
        }
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

| Scenario | Attribute | Min Version |
|---|---|---|
| OS-specific | `[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]` | 3.10 |
| Skip in CI | `[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]` | 3.10 |
| Flaky retry | `[Retry(3)]` | 3.9 |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` | all |

- `[Retry]` should only be used for genuinely flaky **external** dependencies — don't use it to mask race conditions or shared state bugs.
- `[TestCleanup]` always runs after each test, even on failure or exception, making it ideal for resource cleanup.
- You can combine attributes — e.g., a Windows-only test that also retries.
